title: Independent candidate Izzat Javaid Khan wins PP-228 election
content:
ISLAMABAD, Feb 09 (APP): Independent Candidate, Izzat Javaid Khan has won the Punjab Assembly election from PP-228, Lodharan-IV by securing 62,431 votes.
According to the unofficial result issued by the Returning Officer/ECP, his runner-up was Syed Muhammad Rafiuddin Bokhari of Pakistan Muslim League-Nawaz (PML-N) who bagged 43,439 votes.
Overall votersâ€™ turn-out remained 55.32 percent.
